reviews.review: Good movie. Had to make up for a lot of mistakes from the last Jedi and then put an end to all 3 trilogies.

Better than the prequels, I guess. Visually appealing but a mess of half baked ideas that do nothing to develop the character depth that was explored in the last installment. An unsatisfying end to the Skywalker saga.

Absolute garbage! Way to pander to the 14 year fanfic writes on tumblr! Ruined the series, ruined one of the greatest star wars characters ever created, Kylo Ren, no not that mary sue. I was never the biggest star wars fan but as I have a sibling in love with the whole world of star wars I know a lot about it that I never really cared to know and watch her heart break because of how this was butchered! Disgusting.

A fast paced thrill ride that was everything "The Last Jedi" wasn't.  Of course the "top critics"  are mixed.  If I could give this movie 10 stars I would.  Ties up everything nicely and goes out of it's way for some great fan service!

STAR WARS: THE RISE OF SKYWALKER was my favorite movie of the entire Saga. I especially loved the way they incorporated the main characters of the entire saga into the story line.   The way they ended the movie was also great! Definitely a must see!

Too fast, and not enough thought put into the entire movie.       The movie starts out going 100 mph and doesn't slow down for over 2 hours. If it slowed down at all you'd be able to think about the bad decisions the characters make and why they have to go macguffin hunting for most of the movie. The story contradicts existing rules set down by the previous movies, making it hard to understand why things are happening on screen. We won't get any explanations from anyone on screen, such as what is and why we are "Lightspeed Skipping" or where did "Force Healing" suddenly come from. We shouldn't need to read the visual dictionary to know why some things are happening. Rey, Chewie and C-3PO all have big character defining moments in the film, but in the very next scene for each the consequences are undone. There is an entire story line that can be removed and the overall story would be unchanged, from the festival scene to the meeting with Hux can be removed, and nothing would change.     The fact that JJ Abrams walks back almost all of the events from The Last Jedi is the only reason for the half a star.
Very well done, music was intoxicating and the special effects were well, special.
Great movie! It highlights the struggle within the “sinister” characters and the “good” characters. Each ultimately has a choice and redemption is often times the most satisfying moment.

I enjoyed the movie, it’s was entertaining. However there were some things that happened like lightsaber power inconsistencies as an example that nagged at me for the rest of the movie. Despite this, it was still able to entertain me and those who went with me.
Shockingly bad movie. Nothing else to say
